The Wikipedia Search Application is a simple tool that allows users to search for topics directly from Wikipedia.
When a user enters a keyword, the application connects to Wikipedia's API, fetches relevant information, and displays a summary of the topic. 
It helps users quickly access accurate and concise information from one of the largest online encyclopedias.

Technologies used : HTML, CSS, JS, REST API Calls, Bootstrap
Unlock the vast wealth of knowledge on Wikipedia with a custom search
application that delivers relevant and curated results. Quick and easy access to
information has never been easier.
    ● Beautifully presented search results with HTML list elements, styled
    with CSS, Bootstrap, and a responsive design that adapts to any device.
    ● Seamlessly access information with the power of asynchronous fetch
    GET HTTP API calls and the ability to open the desired result in a new
    tab for further reading.
